
// The code concatenates a series of strings and values retrieved from the [.arguments] node. It constructs a sentence using the values of [username], [role], and [country] from the [.arguments] node, separated by static strings. This results in a complete sentence describing a user's identity and origin.
strings.concat
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/username
   .:" is a "
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/role
   .:" from "
   get-value:x:@.arguments/*/country
